Definition.WordDefinition: Mores \Mo"res\ (m[=o]"r[=e]z), n. pl.; sing. {Mos} (m[=o]s). [L.] Customs; habits; esp., moral customs conformity to which is more or less obligatory; customary law. [singular is rarely used] [Webster 1913 Suppl. +PJC]
mores n : (sociology) the conventions that embody the fundamental values of a group
